Main articles: Short-term effects of alcohol, Long-term effects of alcohol, Alcohol and cancer, Alcohol and cardiovascular disease, and Recommended maximum intake of alcoholic beveragesSome studies have suggested that in  moderation, alcohol consumption has significant health benefits.
Chronic effects of alcohol consumption include effects of its metabolism in the liver, its effects on the brain, and effects of addiction (alcoholism).
Alcohol is also a potentially addictive substance, with numerous health effects, and potentially lethal effects of withdrawal.
